Paper Title: A Survey of Abduction in Neural Models and the Feasibility of a Neuroevolution Approach
Paper Author: Timm Holler

A. Summary of the paper:
Examination of the application of neuronal neural networks in neuroscience 

B. Strengths of the paper:
- Well structured

C. Weaknesses of the paper:
- No illustrations of content
- No discussion

D. Short evaluations
D1. Coverage of the Field:
Medium

D2. Depth of the topic:
Low: very short introductions, with little motivation. How does a ANN actually work?

D3. Structure:
Good

D4. Quality of presentation / Clarity:
Medium

D5. Quality of the language:
Medium: well understandable, but written quite colloquially

D6. Critical elaboration of the topic:
Not written yet

E. Detailed comments to the author:
Very general citation of Rojas in 2.2, you might want to cite only specific pages, while explaining ANN

